sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor I as Investigator
  participant UI as NETRA Console
  participant API as Django API
  participant T as Analysis Tools
  participant D as Managed Data Plane

  I->>UI: Select authorized PCAP/PCAPNG and case context
  UI->>API: Upload evidence with authenticated request
  API->>API: Validate extension, size, magic bytes, and type
  API->>API: Compute plaintext SHA-256 identity
  API->>API: Encrypt long-term artifact
  API->>D: Store encrypted evidence and manifest metadata
  API->>T: Analyze temporary authorized working copy
  T-->>API: Packets, protocol logs, sessions, and features
  API->>API: Apply rules and explainable anomaly scoring
  API->>D: Persist case, evidence, findings, and custody events
  API-->>UI: Return case-scoped investigation summary
  I->>UI: Request report, export, or integrity verification
  UI->>API: Generate or verify artifact
  API->>D: Store encrypted report/export
  API->>D: Append access and custody event
  API-->>UI: Deliver reviewable artifact and verification state
  Note right of API: NETRA does not decrypt TLS payloads.<br/>Metadata and behavior are analyzed.
